WEBVTT



00:00:07.584 --> 00:00:09.152
So today is Monday.

00:00:09.024 --> 00:00:15.328
Yesterday was Easter and we had a wonderful time celebrating the resurrection of Jesus Christ together here at Calvary Church.

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:21.280
Throughout Lent, we have been walking with Jesus. We have been focusing our time and our energy

00:00:21.120 --> 00:00:23.744
on spending time with Jesus

00:00:23.488 --> 00:00:25.504
on the journey through Lent.

00:00:25.344 --> 00:00:28.160
And I pray for you that it has been a special time.

00:00:28.160 --> 00:00:33.536
We've now come to the end of Lent. We've celebrated Easter together and I'd like to leave you with

00:00:33.504 --> 00:00:35.776
Kind of maybe one last thought.

00:00:35.712 --> 00:00:36.832
And there's

00:00:36.896 --> 00:00:41.632
A couple of verses at the end of John chapter 20. Yesterday we were in John chapter 20.

00:00:41.472 --> 00:00:43.808
And there's two verses at the end where

00:00:43.552 --> 00:00:45.632
The Apostle John shares

00:00:45.280 --> 00:00:47.232
Kind of his purpose statement.

00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:49.952
for the book of John. Let me read these to you.

00:00:50.144 --> 00:00:54.496
Jesus performed many other signs in the presence of his disciples.

00:00:54.464 --> 00:00:56.480
Which are not recorded in this book.

00:00:56.960 --> 00:01:00.064
But these are written, that you may believe.

00:00:59.904 --> 00:01:02.048
that Jesus is the Messiah

00:01:01.856 --> 00:01:03.232
The son of god.

00:01:03.200 --> 00:01:05.024
and that by believing

00:01:04.928 --> 00:01:06.656
You may have life,

00:01:06.624 --> 00:01:07.904
In his name.

00:01:08.192 --> 00:01:11.808
John tells us here the purpose for why he's written this book.

00:01:11.808 --> 00:01:17.536
He wants you. He wants me. He wants us to believe that Jesus is the Messiah, the Son of God.

00:01:17.920 --> 00:01:19.552
And in doing so,

00:01:19.744 --> 00:01:23.392
We don't just receive a series of teachings.

00:01:23.648 --> 00:01:27.808
All other world religions are based on a series of teachings.

00:01:27.936 --> 00:01:29.248
Mohammed,

00:01:29.024 --> 00:01:32.256
In Islam, they proclaimed teachings to follow.

00:01:32.352 --> 00:01:33.376
Buddha.

00:01:33.216 --> 00:01:35.712
From Buddhism, there's a series of teachings.

00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:39.264
Confucius provides teachings for people to follow.

00:01:39.648 --> 00:01:41.632
With Christianity, it's much different.

00:01:41.984 --> 00:01:44.064
Jesus offers himself.

00:01:44.288 --> 00:01:45.664
It's a person.

00:01:45.728 --> 00:01:48.416
You receive a relationship with Jesus.

00:01:48.448 --> 00:01:50.080
Yeah, there's teachings.

00:01:50.272 --> 00:01:51.968
But they're secondary.

00:01:51.776 --> 00:01:54.112
To the person of Jesus Christ.

00:01:54.336 --> 00:01:59.296
So as we end this time of Lent and celebrating in Easter,

00:01:59.296 --> 00:02:00.768
I just want to remind you,

00:02:00.896 --> 00:02:03.136
Continue your walk with Jesus.

00:02:03.328 --> 00:02:04.960
The person of christ.

00:02:05.152 --> 00:02:07.648
Recognizing that he is the Messiah.

00:02:07.744 --> 00:02:10.048
The son of the living god.
